Sentencas: La1.0Sr1.0FeO4+delta (LSF1010) material with K2NiF4 structure was synthesized via the glycine nitrate process and characterized by XRD.
Titulo: Preparation and Electrochemical Properties of La1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Composite materials La1.0Sr1.0FeO4+delta-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (LSF1010-SDC) were prepared and characterized as cathode for intermediate temperature SOFCs (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Preparation and Electrochemical Properties of La1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: XRD results show that no reaction occurs between La1.0Sr1.0FeO4+delta and SDC at 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Preparation and Electrochemical Properties of La1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: For LSF1010-30% SDC electrode, SEM results suggest that better microstructure is obtained and the electrode possesses good contact with the electrolyte after sintering at 1000 degrees C for 2 h. Compared with the pure LSF1010 cathode, LSF1010 SDC exhibits better cathodic properties.
Titulo: Preparation and Electrochemical Properties of La1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In particular, the LSF1010-30% SDC electrode possesses the best catalytic activity for oxygen reduction.
Titulo: Preparation and Electrochemical Properties of La1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: At 700 degrees C, the polarization resistance of the LSF1010-30% SDC cathode is 0.80 Omega.cm(2) on SDC electrolyte, which is nearly five times lower than that of the pure LSF1010 electrode, and the lowest polarization overpotential is -86
Titulo: Preparation and Electrochemical Properties of La1.0Sr1.0FeO4+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Composite Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
